OL,3,CGovernment's #200 million software
OL,4,Cdeal 'totally inadequate'
OL,6,FHe explains: "The States didn't know
OL,7,Fwhat systems it was running. It didn't
OL,8,Fknow, so there's no way you can draft
OL,9,Fa contract if you don't know and that
OL,10,Fis down to senior management's
OL,11,Fresponsibility.
OL,13,F"We demand a basic level of competence
OL,14,Fand there is simply no competence.
OL,15,FThis demonstrates that we have people
OL,16,Funfortunately running public services
OL,17,Fthat simply have no idea what they're
OL,18,Fdoing."
